h3. Summary
The *notificationinstance* table is queried every time a Mail Handler processes an email, and there aren't any indexes defined for this table.

Here is an example query.
{code:sql}
SELECT ID, notificationtype, SOURCE, emailaddress, MESSAGEID FROM public.notificationinstance WHERE MESSAGEID=XXXX
{code}

In a large instance with many users and emails to process, this can potentially cause performance issues with additional load on the DB server, as the number of logical reads necessary to run the query is very high.

h3. Suggestion
Define an index on {{MESSAGEID}}. This has been found to considerably reduce the CPU footprint of the queries.

